Security note — token storage

Never store the access token in localStorage or sessionStorage. These are accessible to any JavaScript on the page and vulnerable to XSS attacks. Store in Pinia (memory) only. The token is lost on page refresh but the Nuxt app plugin calls /api/v1/auth/refresh on initialisation to get a new one silently using the httpOnly cookie.

Definition of done — ST-08

Form renders correctly on desktop Chrome and Android Chrome on a 7-inch tablet. All client validation works before submission. Successful registration redirects to settings. API error messages display per field. Token is in Pinia store. Character counter works on description field. Page is fully responsive.
